      <outline text="Next Gen iPods might use widgets" MediaLinks="The Next Gen iPods, might have widgets?  &lt;http://www.macosrumors.com/20060322A.php&gt;">
        <outline text="The former would be in line with previous rumors about a 16:10 widescreen iPod with its entire front face dedicated to a four-inch touchscreen, with the traditional iPod scroll-wheel interface implemented in the operating system as a touch-screen widget."/>
      </outline>
      <outline text="Doomsday Widget" MediaLinks="Doomsday Widget &lt;http://www.crazyapplerumors.com/?p=502&gt;">
        <outline text="“ Concerned sources close to Konfabulator creator Arlo Rose indicate that the Mac developer is working on a Doomsday widget that will utterly destroy the Macintosh desktop. In a fit of pique over the announcement that Apple will include functionality similar to Konfabulator in the upcoming update to OS X code-named Tiger, Rose is adopting a scorched-earth strategy.”"/>
      </outline>
      <outline text="Dashboard Detection in Safari" MediaLinks="Dashboard Detection in Safari  &lt;http://www.macrumors.com/pages/2005/09/20050928125215.shtml&gt;">
        <outline text="“ Appleinsider reports that upcoming Mac OS X 10.4.3 updates appear to include special Dashboard buttons in the newest version of Safari.”"/>
      </outline>
    </outline>
    <outline text="Interview and Listener Feedback">
      <outline text="Widgetarium is one of the best widget making apps out there today!">
        <outline text="Widgetarium is an IDE for developing Dashboard Widgets. It includes everything you need to make a Widget, including: Syntax coloring Editor, with function pop-up navigation, auto completion, regex search/replace, etc… Graphics generates to make the panels and icons&#10;Project manager to manage files, build packages, set Info.plist files&#10;Dashboard emulator and interactive JavaScript interpreter to test and inspect the Widget DOM Source level debugger, complete with breakpoints, view/set local and global variables&#10;&#10;Online Widget and JavaScript documentation&#10;Special custom native code extensions&#10;And much more…"/>
      </outline>
    </outline>
